e acquiring firm avoids the risk and cost of internal innovation. In addition, ac
quisitions provide more predictable returns on investments than internal new prod
uct development. Acquisitions are a much quicker path than internal development t
o enter a new market, and they are a means of gaining new capabilities for the ac
quiring firm. (4) }\plain \i \f1
\fs22
